2. These essays offer different and, in some cases, heterodox interpretations that will serve as a basis for future discussions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Poetry.2bisacsh1 aAnderson, William S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGalinsky, G. Karl, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGalinsky, Karl, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLuck, Georg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReckford, Kenneth J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSegal, Erich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292772830423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292772830/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK